snippet.textDisplay:
Not at the races today, the rangers definitely deserved that win. Poor penalty from Christie, right at the height for any keeper to get to that. Lucky on the goal to be honest too. We'll come back from the break in a better frame of mind, and go on from there. Well taken goal from Kent, but his celebration leaves a lot to be desired. Morelos, took long enough to get that second yellow, and still can't leave the field without being a bellend. He's ruining the good work he's been putting in on his discipline in the past two games alone. He will go on to be a great player if he keeps that under wraps. 

Katic goal, shouldn't even have been a corner in the first place, it came off a rangers player last too. Either way, it should have been dealt with much better, he was given far too much space to get that head on goal.

For those complaining about the edit, look at the stats, Celtic had more possession, more shots, and more corners. We just didn't finish them off. Your lot closed the gaps very well though, and restricted our passing game, hats off. And Davis was clearly your MotM, cleared two goals from the line.

On to the next one! Enjoy your break folks!

snippet.textDisplay: An interesting game. It is clear that the last two games these reams have played against one another...that rangers were the better team...although celtic robbed them of cup victory.  Rangers wanted to win this fixture more than celtic...and this time they did.  Both of these sides wouldn't last a season in the English Championship...but still dominate Scottish football because everyone in Scotland supports them. Teams like Ross County, St. Johnstone, Livingston, Hamilton and Kilmarnock regularly get crowds of well below 3,000 fans...and the Linesman gets paid more than the players.  It's a sham league...and consequently a sham competition.  Morrelos and Eduard get paid more each week than the aforementioned teams...combined...pay their players...and they are just there to be cannon fodder for rangers and celtic.  The main problem for celtic now...is that rangers appointed a manager who knows a lot about top level football...at the highest levels...and they soldier on with a manager who got his job back after abandoning celtic to fly south for more cash...got relegated and sacked and then swept back in after a time with hibbs.  Rangers look like they will win the tin pot league...and stop Celtic's domination of this comedy league.  Sctsmen should abandon this crap...and go and watch the Highland League...where teams are very evenly matched...and resourced.  It looks like ''weearrapeepoll''...are getting back on top.  Hail hail....seems to be....fading somewhat.
